  "texts": [
    "Overview of literature on assortment optimization under further parametric choice models including exponomial choice, Markov chain choice, single transition, locational choice, probabilistic choice, attraction demand, and general choice models publications under the NL model, 8 studies under the MMNL model, and 5 publications under the Markov chain choice model.",
    "Moreover, as can be seen in Tables 2, 3, 4, and 5, most authors analyse the nonrobust assortment problem-only 6 out of 82 publications who study the assortment problem under a parametric choice model follow a robust approach.",
    "Out of these six studies, five consider the assortment problem under the MNL model; only one publication on robust assortment optimization utilizes the Markov chain choice model.",
    "Moreover, all of these studies on robust assortment optimization under a parametric choice model consider single-purchase settings without constraint or with cardinality constraint.",
    "Similarly, the majority of the 82 studies deal with the static assortment problem; only 30 out of 82 studies consider the dynamic problem, though the fraction of researchers studying the dynamic version increases in recent years."
  ],
